Incident.Summary: 2 Vehicle collision hit and run, DUI, assault on police and EMS at barrack

IncidentSuppNarrative.NarrativeText:
Maryland State Police Centreville Barrack DUI S-23-1067
Case Number 23-MSP-019762
Trooper First Class Selba #6315
Events recorded on AXON equipment.

Certifications:
-National Highway Safety Transportation Administration (NHSTA) to conduct Standardized Field Sobriety Test (SFST)
-Certified Preliminary Breath Test (PBT) operator
-Certified RADAR & LIDAR operator
-Certified to utilize License Plate Recognition (LPR)
-Advance Roadside Impairment Driving Enforcement (ARIDE)
-Traffic Safety Specialist Level I

Suspect:
Christopher David Parsley Jr(W/M 09/20/1986)
11029 Brindley Dr. Worton, MD 21678
Height: 5’10” Weight: 160lbs Hair: Brown Eyes: Brown

Weather Conditions:
I observed the weather conditions to be clear and approximately 89 degrees.

Phase I (Vehicle in Motion)
On 06/02/2023 at 1513 hours the MSP – Centreville Barrack received the first 911 phone call in reference to a possible DUI driver in a silver Chevrolet pickup truck and at 1526 hours received a second 911 phone call in reference to the same silver Chevrolet pickup truck who was drunk driving; the second caller was the girlfriend of drunk driver, Brittany Nicole Walker (W/F 07/31/1994), and she was following him, Christopher David Parsley Jr(W/M 09/20/1986). Walker was giving updated locations as they traveled south on MD -213 in the Chestertown area. At 1545 QACSO Deputy Bradley #0198 messaged me, TFC Selba #6315, on the computer stating he saw the BOLO and it had pulled into the Milano’s off MD-213 in Chestertown, Queen Anne’s County, MD. Deputy Bradley stated he saw the white male driver look over his shoulder to look at him; he had no passengers. Deputy Bradley then messaged me he was going to wait for him just south by Rolphs Wharf Rd. At approximately 1548 hours the MSP – Centreville Barrack received another 911 phone call in reference to a 2 vehicle collision hit and run where the new model Chevrolet Silverado with a MD temporary tag had struck the caller’s tractor trailer on S/B MD-213 at Schrader Rd, Chestertown, MD 21620. The tractor trailer truck driver, Bryan Jeffrey Sharp (W/M 07/09/1962), stated while he was traveling S/B and about to make the right turn onto Schrader Rd, the Silverado had started to pass him on the right shoulder and before he knew it struck the tractor trailer’s front passenger side; he informed 911 that the Silverado had a flat tire and was fleeing the scene.

Deputy Bradley utilized MSP – Centreville’s radio to notify us he had located the Silverado on S/B MD-213 north of Rolphs Wharf, it matched the BOLO’s descriptions and had a flat tire. I, TFC Selba #6315, responded accordingly in marked MSP unit S-13 wearing my full class C uniform with an AXON body worn camera (BWC) and I arrived on scene at 1553 hours and observed a silver 2018 Chevrolet Silverado bearing a temporary MD registration “T1357009” disabled on the right shoulder of S/B MD-213 with damage to its driver’s side and the back left tire was completely off the rim of the wheel. Phillips Towing was utilized for Silverado. S/T Nickerson #5702 responded to the tractor trailer and stated there was damage to the front passenger side of the truck.

Phase II (Personal Contact)
Deputy Bradley and the white male were standing between the Silverado and his patrol car. Deputy Bradley confirmed this was the truck from the BOLO, it was the truck he observed, and that the white male was the driver; the sole occupant of the truck. I observed the white male stumble forward, use his phone, and then almost fall into the Deputy’s patrol vehicle. I informed the male of who I was, my ID number, and that my body worn camera was recording. I then asked the white male if he was hurt. He denied being hurt and insisted that the Silverado got a blowout. I confronted him about hitting a tractor trailer, he stated his “old lady” was driving and the tractor trailer swerved into her lane.

While standing still the white male swayed and stumbled backwards. He slurred his speech when stating, “My old lady was driving the truck.” He then constantly leaned on the Deputy’s hood for balance. The white male was constantly looking north, he would step into the grass, and then stumble when walking back onto the roadway. I observed another white SUV parked behind my patrol vehicle, the white male stated that was his “old lady”. He claimed her mother had picked her up to go get a tire, I only observed 1 female in the white SUV. The white male slurred his speech the entire time and swayed while standing still.

I confirmed with him again that he was not hurt and he did not need EMS attention. I then positively identified him by his name and date of birth to be Christopher David Parsley Jr (W/M 09/20/1986). Parsley Jr had his hands in his pockets, swayed, slurred his speech, and I began to detect the odor of an alcohol beverage on his breath. I observed his eyes to bloodshot, watery, and glassy. Parsley Jr slurred his speech very noticeably when saying his street name of Brindley Drive and when he stated he was going to Centreville to pick up his son.

While I was gathering this information, Deputy Bradley interviewed Parsley Jr’s girlfriend, Brittany Walker (the 2nd 911 caller for the DUI BOLO). Walker stated she was not in the Silverado, she was not driving, and that Parsley Jr was driving. Walker knew he had been drinking at his house in Worton and he was driving to Centreville, she was following him and calling 911 to get him stopped.

I requested for Parsley Jr to remove his hands from his pockets. He complied. I then asked for consent to pat him down for weapons, he agreed. During the pat down I detected the odor of an alcoholic beverage on his person. While I was calling out Parsley Jr’s information, in his spontaneous utterance, he said, “her and her mother where behind me and she said I had a blowout so…” Again, Parsley Jr would sway while standing still. I asked how much did he have to drink and stated, “None.”

Phase III (Pre-Arrest Screening)
I am certified by the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration (NHSTA) to conduct SFST’s. I asked for Parsley Jr’s consent to perform Standardized Field Sobriety Tests and he refused.

Horizontal Gaze Nystagmus (HGN) REFUSED
Walk and Turn REFUSED
One Leg Stand REFUSED
Preliminary Breath Test (PBT) REFUSED

Arrest
Based on the following, I had reason to believe Carroll was driving a motor vehicle under the influence of alcohol:
  • Two separate 911 phone calls in reference to a possible drunk driver, one being the girlfriend.
  • Driving off road while passing another vehicle.
  • Sideswiping a tractor trailer.
  • Leaving the scene of a motor vehicle accident resulting property damage.
  • Attempting to drive with a flat tire to the point where the tire tread is coming off the rim.
  • Stumbling while walking short distances.
  • Swaying while standing still.
  • Odor of an alcoholic beverage on his breath.
  • Odor of an alcoholic beverage on his person.
  • Bloodshot, watery, and glassy eyes.
  • Slurred speech.
  • Mix-matching his statements about who was driving.
Parsley Jr was arrested for driving under the influence of alcohol at 1606 hours. A preliminary search was conducted on scene and it revealed he had nothing in his mouth. At 1609 hours I attempted to read Parsley Jr his Miranda Warnings and he began to walk away from me. I took control of Parsley Jr’s right upper arm to stop him from walking away. Parsley Jr began hostile and argumentative. The odor of an alcoholic beverage became more prevalent as he argued with me. At 1610 hours Parsley Jr stated he knew his rights and did not waive them. While escorting Parsley Jr towards my patrol vehicle, he was unsteady on his feet and stumbled while navigating around the Deputy’s patrol vehicle. Parsley Jr was placed in the front passenger seat of my patrol vehicle. Another QACSO Deputy stood by with Parsley Jr. Once the Barrack updated me with Parsley Jr’s MVA returns, I learned had no license (ID only) with a 3 year alcohol restriction, court ordered alcohol restriction and a court ordered ignition interlock, revocation indefinitely, and 34 other violations on his driving record leading up to his license withdrawal. While in my patrol vehicle, I gathered a witness statement form and Parsley Jr constantly slurred his speech and proclaimed Walker was driving; the odor of an alcoholic beverage fill the passenger compartment of my patrol vehicle.

When I approached the Silverado to see if it was equipped with an ignition interlock (it did not) I detected the odor of marijuana emanating from within the vehicle. At 1620 hours a probable cause search of the vehicle Silverado revealed one glass jar containing one (1) clear plastic baggie containing greenish brown vegetable matter, suspected marijuana and more loose amount of suspected marijuana. I observed the greenish brown vegetable matter to be marijuana and to be associated with the possession and consumption of a Controlled Dangerous Substance based on my training, knowledge, and experience as a Maryland State Trooper. My training consists of successful completion of the Maryland State Police Academy. I have also completed a MSP Street Level Narcotics class, MSP PACE Team Interdiction Seminar, and a Traffic Stop Tactics/Drug Interdiction Class.

When securing the CDS back into my patrol vehicle, I heard Parsley Jr arguing with the other Deputy calling him an “asshole” and cussing at him about the handcuffs. I then walked back to the white SUV and spoke to Walker, she was in tears and confirmed she was one of the 911 callers. Walker confirmed she was not driving the Silverado, Parsley Jr was drinking in Worton, and was driving to Centreville to pick up his son.

When I got back into my patrol vehicle, Parsley Jr began acting like an irrational drunk; constantly arguing with me and repeating his questions. At 1628 hours Parsley Jr was transported to the MSP – Centreville Barrack. While en route to the Barrack, Parsley Jr displayed a wide variety of emotions, trying to talk to me about personal matters, proclaiming his sequence of events, then became agitated asking the same questions over and over about the charges. While Parsley Jr shouted at me, the odor of an alcoholic beverage became stronger. Once at the Barrack at 1644 hours, Parsley Jr became even more hostile and used the phrase towards me, “…acting like a fucking nigger” when I asked him to walk towards the Barrack’s back door.

While attempting to read Parsley Jr his DR-15 Advice of Rights in the DUI processing room, Parsley Jr continued to act irrational. He was passive aggressive towards every instruction given to him. Parsley Jr called Walker on his cell phone, they constantly argued. When he got off the phone he threw his phone at the wall when attempting to place it on the desk. He then grabbed his keys of the desk, attempted to put them in his left short pocket, and missed, dropping them on the floor. Displaying poor fine motor skills. Parsley Jr failed to obey the commands to sit back down and instead a cussed at me saying, “Come on fucking, gimme the shit and come on.”  When attempting to read the DR-15, Parsley Jr constantly repeated the word “innocent”. He then constantly cussed, shouted, and argued with me about his innocence. Parsley Jr then attempted to walk past me and through SGT Wiley #6097. SGT Wiley had to physically stop Parsley Jr from leaving the processing room by placing his hand on Parsley Jr’s chest briefly. Parsley Jr then stuck his pointer finger in his mouth several times and attempted to put his in my ear while I was trying to read the DR-15. He then constantly shoved his hands in my face, blocking my view from the DR-15. When I asked him if wanted to submit to the intoximeter test he said, “No, fuck you and fuck this law…” It took me 17 minutes to read the DR-15 before Parsley Jr refused to submit to a test. When I attempted to have Parsley Jr sign the DR-15, he took the form and threw it on the floor. It will be marked as a refusal to sign.

When attempting to escort Parsley Jr into the cell, he grabbed his cellphone and keys. When instructing him it was not going in the cell with him, he pulled away. I attempted to take the cellphone out of Parsley Jr’s hand and he started pull away from me. I then held onto the cellphone and held the inside of Parsley Jr’s left bicep. Parsley Jr then yelled in my face “Ow! My arm” and then smirked. SGT Wiley attempted to talk Parsley Jr into walking towards the cell and became very passive aggressive. I retrieve a paper bag to put Parsley Jr’s belongings in, he said, “getting the fucking bag outta here faggot… I’m just asking you to shut the fuck up.” It took 7 minutes for Parsley Jr to walk into the cell. At 1714 hours Parsley Jr was placed into the cell, where he immediately took his hat off and threw it at the wall.

At 1746 hours I was notified to come back into the barrack. I observed SGT Wiley standing at the opening of the cell with the door open trying to get Parsley Jr’s attention. Parsley Jr was slumped over laying on the cell’s bench breathing heavily. When SGT Wiley approached him, Parsley Jr rolled off the edge, SGT Wiley attempted to stop his fall. Moments later Parsley Jr came to, took several deep breaths and asked, “Where the fuck am I?” His face was red and he was sweating. He began stating he needed his medicine stating he has seizures, he was unable to tell us what medication he takes. At 1749 hours I observed Parsley Jr dropped his head to the floor. Parsley Jr then appeared to come and go with his alertness and he kicked off his shoes and began kicking the concrete bench in the cell, he subsequently injured his toes from kicking the bench barefoot. Parsley Jr would then yell as he got into the fetal position and begin kicking and head-butting the bench. When SGT Wiley attempted to prevent him from hitting the bench, Parsley Jr slammed his head on the floor and flailed about, again he subsequently injured himself from hitting his head from these actions. SGT Wiley attempted to prevent any further self-inflicted injuries. Parsley Jr would yell indecipherable phrases. Parsley Jr would periodically thrash about and then become alert.

SGT Wiley attempted to ask Parsley Jr what medications he was taking, he riddled off some over the counter medications. At 1752 hours Parsley Jr crawled into the corner of the cell against the cell’s bench and wall. Parsley Jr would breathe heavily while stating he cannot breathe. Parsley Jr then began to cry, yell, and bang his head on the bench. At 1753 hours Queen Anne’s EMS Paramedic 400 arrived (Run #2023-00002119) and they attempted to build a rapport. Parsley Jr would then thrash about again attempting to hit his head on the bench and wall. Paramedic Casey Amos and EMT Terry Williams attempt to prevent inadvertent injury. Parsley Jr then scooted forward and started hitting the back of his head against the cell’s toilet behind him. EMT Williams laid him down on the cell’s floor while Parsley Jr cussed, yelled, and then cried. When Parsley Jr attempted to get up and was instructed to remain seated and calm down, Parsley Jr would tell us to “Fuck off! … Get the fuck off of me!”

At 1757 hours Parsley Jr was speaking full sentences and demanding that we called Brittany (Walker). Shortly after, Parsley Jr went limp, EMT Williams guided him down, and Paramedic Amos administered a sedative. At 1759 hours I retrieve my agency issued digital camera to take photographs of Parsley Jr injuries on his head, legs, and feet. At 1800 hours TFC Mulhearn #6494 arrived. At this time Parsley Jr started yelling he wanted to go home as everyone was asking him to get onto the stretcher. I then heard Parsley Jr say, “I’m going the fuck home…bitch get off me!” and the I heard rustling. Parsley Jr was pushing, swinging, and shoving SGT Wiley and TFC Mulhearn in an attempt the exit the cell. I then placed my camera down in the processing room and made my way into the cell where I observed TFC Mulhearn, SGT Wiley, and EMT Williams attempting to control Parsley Jr as he was actively pushing them away in an effort to exit the cell. I then took control of Parsley Jr’s right wrist and right elbow. TFC Mulhearn announced we needed to handcuff him. I was able to control Parsley Jr’s upper right arm and push his right hand behind his back for TFC Mulhearn to get a handcuff on at 1801 hours. Parsley Jr then started to lean forward, everyone gently eased Parsley Jr to the ground on his chest. When Parsley Jr started thrashing about and kicking, my BWC came off. Everyone announced for Parsley Jr to relax and to stop kicking.

I was able to get my BWC back on at 1802 hours. I then observed Parsley Jr start kicking TFC Mulhearn and calling him a “faggot”. When TFC Mulhearn attempted to stand up, Parsley Jr kicked him again. TFC Mulhearn got Parsley Jr’s blood on his uniform pants. SGT Wiley and EMT Williams were able to get Parsley Jr onto the stretcher. Parsley Jr then locked eyes with TFC Mulhearn and said, “What are you rolling your eyes about faggot? Take these damn cuffs off, let’s do this…” While everyone was strapping Parsley Jr into the stretcher, Parsley Jr constantly made threats towards TFC Mulhearn and cussed at him. Parsley Jr would then attempt to get out of the restraints, kick EMT Williams, in an effort to charge at TFC Mulhearn. Parsley Jr then spat in TFC Mulhearn’s direction but it hit EMT Williams.

At 1804 hours Parsley Jr was taken out of the Barrack on the stretcher, he constantly yelled, cried, and attempted to get out of the restraints. I then took photographs of the cell where Parsley Jr’s blood spots were left. I also retrieved his shoes and hat. I attempted to take photographs of Parsley Jr injuries while in the ambulance. Parsley Jr constantly kept raising his foot to block the camera. At 1807 hours I rode in the back of the ambulance where Parsley Jr constantly argued, yelled at the paramedics, and started to unbuckle the restraints. Parsley Jr would then get his hands down under his legs and in the front. Shortly thereafter Parsley Jr passed out. While Parsley Jr was asleep I took more photographs of his injuries to his head, legs, and feet. TPR Severa #7374 followed PA400 as we transported Parsley Jr to the University of MD Shore Medical Center at Easton. At 1844 hours we arrived at the hospital where he would be released from police custody.

On 06/03/2023 Deputy Bradley provided me with his field case reports narrative, it will be attached. I also completed an application for charges an obtained an arrest warrant for Parsley Jr. The recovered CDS was stored in the Barrack's temporary storage room. The suspected marijuana was processed, weighed to be 10.9 grams, and stored per MSP policy and procedures. Parsley Jr will be issued a civil citation for personal amount of cannabis (1Z42292181).

On 06/07/2023 Parsley Jr was arrested by Kent County Sheriff's Office for violation of probation from a DUI case in 2021, KCSO served my warrant as well. On 06/09/2023 I responded Kent County's Detention Center to serve Parsley Jr his civil citation, DR-15, and DR-15A. Parsley Jr signed the necessary documents. I also provided Parsley Jr with his copy of the beginning portion of the ACRS report (exchange of information) with his case number.

Events occurred in Queen Anne’s County, Talbot County, and Kent County, Maryland.
